org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.as.codegen

Class ControlFlowContextManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.as.codegen.ControlFlowContextManager

  • public class ControlFlowContextManager
extends Object
    The ControlFlowContextManager is the code generator's keeper of active control-flow contexts and the associated (implicit in the configuration of contexts) model of the scope stack. Control-flow contexts come in several varieties:
    • Ordinary control-flow contexts, established by a labeled statement or a statement with break/continue semantics.
    • Exception-handling contexts, established by try with a catch or finally.
    • With statements.
    These various types of context have few common elements, aside from participating in the model of control flow and the scope stack, so this class manages the active configuration of contexts and embodies the code generator's control-flow and scope stack model.
